rComments: Her teaching style is alarming at first - it feels like she starts halfway through. Once you get used to that, though, it is actually pretty effective. She likes to mislead the class until someone calls her out on it. I don't think the way she does (graphs and numbers), but she managed to make it all quite accessible.
She has a rigid way of teaching - clearly has an agenda in mind that she can't be distracted from. That said, she's smart and funny. She goes through hundreds of cases really quickly - be prepared.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Excellent prof: very good at drawing links between cases.  Going to class is a MUST: you really won't get her take on the case law by only reading the case book.

Lectures are generally clear and concise, and she has a way of drawing connections between the various cases that helps clarify the material.  Workload was kept very reasonable (had an ambitious reading list at the beginning which she cut down as the semester went on).
Totally awesome! This is the only class where I never look at my watch wondering 'how much longer do we have to go?'
